    On arriving at the villa, you can't help but be impressed - it is beautiful, luxurious and exceptionally well maintained. The hotel manager is so professional and efficient. He offered us an upgrade on our room so you can only imagine our delight.
    Breakfast was served every morning outside on the terrace overlooking the pool area. We had the best mint tea in Morocco at Dar Tanja! The villa has a few lounge areas where you can relax and enjoy some tea and just contemplate. Stunning garden area as well.
    Dar Tanja offers a massage service on site and this was booked via the hotel manager. And what an amazing massage it was. I felt like I floated to dinner later that evening.
    The villa is located outside of the city centre in a very upmarket leafy green suburb. It was a short taxi ride away from where ever we needed to be. At 10 - 20 MAD a trip it was a pleasure and I am glad we stayed outside of the town centre. The peace and tranquility and luxury is worth it.
    We stayed for 2 nights and I wish we had had stayed longer. Highly recommended hotel! Our stay at Dar Tanja was definitely one of the highlights of our Morocco trip!
